00:37:51,989 --> 00:37:54,909
 So you might choose as a greedy algorithm,

484
00:37:55,949 --> 00:37:57,750
 if you can go up, go up.

485
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:02,760
 If you can't go up, you stop, right?

486
00:38:03,079 --> 00:38:05,480
 So whenever you get a choice, you go up.

487
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:13,869
 And so if I start here, I could, right in the middle,

488
00:38:14,530 --> 00:38:18,170
 maybe say, all right, it's not up, but it's not down either.

489
00:38:18,170 --> 00:38:26,059
 so I'll go either left or right and let's say I go right so I come to here

490
00:38:26,059 --> 00:38:31,619
 and then I'll just make my way up to the top of the hill making a locally optimal

491
00:38:31,619 --> 00:38:37,260
 decision head up at each point and I'll get here and I'll say well now any place

492
00:38:37,260 --> 00:38:43,300
 I go takes me to a lower point so I don't want to do it right because the

493
00:38:43,300 --> 00:38:49,820
 greedy algorithm says never go backwards so I'm here and I'm happy on the other

494
00:38:49,820 --> 00:38:55,500
 On the other hand, if I had gone here for my first step,

495
00:38:56,119 --> 00:38:59,400
 then my next step up would take me up, up, up.

496
00:38:59,579 --> 00:39:00,420
 I'd get to here.

497
00:39:01,539 --> 00:39:07,940
 And I'd stop and say, OK, no way to go but down.

498
00:39:08,099 --> 00:39:09,059
 I don't want to go down.

499
00:39:09,139 --> 00:39:09,500
 I'm done.

500
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:13,840
 And what I would find is I'm at a local maximum rather

501
00:39:13,840 --> 00:39:14,980
 than a global maximum.

502
00:39:17,329 --> 00:39:19,769
 And that's the problem with greedy algorithms,

503
00:39:19,769 --> 00:39:25,010
 that you can get stuck at a local optimal point

504
00:39:26,250 --> 00:39:29,110
 and not get to the best one.

505
00:39:30,389 --> 00:39:32,429
 Now, we could ask the question,

506
00:39:35,969 --> 00:39:38,329
 can I just say, don't worry about it.

507
00:39:38,409 --> 00:39:40,809
 Density, say, will always get me the best answer.

508
00:39:43,570 --> 00:39:45,230
 I've tried a different experiment.

509
00:39:45,349 --> 00:39:46,909
 Let's say I'm feeling expansive

510
00:39:46,909 --> 00:39:49,230
 and I'm going to allow myself 1,000 calories.

511
00:39:49,230 --> 00:40:10,769
 stories. Well, here what we see is the winner will be greedy by value. Happens to find a

512
00:40:10,769 --> 00:40:20,429
 better answer, 424 instead of 413. So there is no way to know in advance. Sometimes this

513
00:40:20,429 --> 00:40:26,650
 definition of best might work. Sometimes that might work. Sometimes no definition of best

514
00:40:26,650 --> 00:40:30,869
 best will work, and you can't get to a good solution.

515
00:40:31,030 --> 00:40:32,670
 Or you can get to a good solution,

516
00:40:32,809 --> 00:40:34,849
 you can't get to an optimal solution

517
00:40:34,849 --> 00:40:35,829
 with the greedy algorithm.

518
00:40:36,909 --> 00:40:40,690
 On Wednesday, we'll talk about how do you actually

519
00:40:40,690 --> 00:40:44,670
 guarantee finding an optimal solution in a better way

520
00:40:44,670 --> 00:40:45,409
 than brute force.

521
00:40:46,329 --> 00:40:47,070
 See you then.

